element.value: Basic MyCode page that uses the post parser.

For those who don't know. [quote='WikiPedia']MyBB, [i]originally[/i] MyBulletinBoard, is a [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_and_open-source_software]free and open source[/url] [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forum_software]forum software[/url] which is developed by the MyBB Group. It is written in PHP, supports [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MySQL]MySQL[/url], [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PostgreSQL]PostgreSQL[/url] and [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SQLite]SQLite[/url] as [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Database]database[/url] systems and has database [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Failover]failover[/url] support. It is licensed under the [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGPL]LGPL[/url].[/quote] :)
